OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FPhone firms row over       
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fcustomers overpaying       
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Virgin Media O2 has accused rival      
OL,6, mobile operators of not doing enough to
OL,7, help customers move onto cheaper       
OL,8, monthly tariffs.                       
OL,10,FThe phone giant says other firms are   
OL,11,F"swindling" people by keeping them on  
OL,12,Frates that cover the cost of a handset,
OL,13,Feven after they have finished paying   
OL,14,Ffor the phone.                         
OL,16,FThe accusation has prompted a row with 
OL,17,Fother firms including EE and Vodafone. 
OL,19,FThey say Virgin Media O2's claims are  
OL,20,Fmisleading and confusing.              
